Description:
A Californian Dream In Sought After Street
Superbly located in a quiet tree-lined pocket of family friendly Coburg, this pretty as a picture 1920’s Californian bungalow is a sensitively modernised and extended period residence. Featuring burnished baltic pine floors, ducted heating and fresh decor, it includes two front bedrooms, main with spacious mirrored BIR’s, pristine bathroom, formal lounge with a heritage fireplace and polished timber mantle, air-conditioned dining room, generous timber kitchen, third bedroom, spacious family room, laundry and powder room.
• Excellently positioned in sought after family area
• Modernised Californian Bungalow retaining some period features
• Immaculately presented property with strong street presence
• 2 car lock-up garage plus additional off-street street parking
• Close to shops, schools, transport, with easy Citylink access
From the cultivated front garden to the well sized back-yard with BBQ and double lock-up garage, this delightful family home is an absolute gem with a beautiful street presence, providing excellent proximity to quality schools, local shopping, trams, trains and a rapid CBD commute via Citylink.
Insights: 87 Phillips St, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Perfect Location, Amazing Potential
First time offered in nearly 70 years, this attractive Californian Bungalow provides a world of opportunities for those looking to renovate and extend (STCA) in a coveted Coburg neighbourhood just north of Brunswick's border. Impeccably-presented throughout, the home's current floorplan includes two bedrooms (large master) and neat bathroom, light-filled lounge and adjoining dining room through to the kitchen/meals area. Features include gas heating, high ceilings, original lead-light windows, plus a brick-paved undercover patio and expansive backyard garden with plenty of room to expand. Walking distance to Nicholson Street/Moreland Road trams, local parks and Merri Creek trails, it's also close to primary and secondary schools, as well as easy access to Moreland Station, Sydney Road shops, cafes and restaurants. Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Under Offer
Victorian Grandeur with Outstanding Versatility - Two homes in one! On a huge block of land (900sqm+), this period showpiece makes an ideal choice for large/extended families or blue-chip investors seeking a dual-income stream with its extended design, first-class features and self-contained villa at the rear. Beyond its grand facade, the home's extended floorplan comprises four bedrooms (extra-large master with WIR and contemporary ensuite), equally-stylish main bathroom, vast open-plan living/dining complemented by a quality kitchen with stainless steel benchtops and Blanco/Asko appliances. Other features include ducted heating throughout and split-system a/c (living area and all bedrooms), towering ceilings, polished floorboards, solar power, large modern laundry, plus undercover entertaining deck, expansive backyard garden and secure carport via side driveway. Add to this self-contained 1BR villa including stylish bathroom, open lounge/dining and kitchen with dishwasher, heating/cooling, laundry facilities, undercover deck and private garden. In a quiet cul-de-sac location just north of Brunswick's border, it's walking distance to Moreland Station and Sydney Road trams, close to local schools and parks, hospital/medical precinct as well as the area's specialty shops, cool cafes and renowned restaurants.

Description:
Watch Your Future Shine
Newly updated, flaunting a fresh interior, spacious floor plan and modern stainless steel appliances, this three bedroom, two bathroom residence delivers desirable living in the popular Pentridge precinct. Lush landscaping, generous living and dining domains and a fully equipped kitchen, with expansive counters and appliances from names including Bosch, ensure that relaxing and entertaining will be easy. Fully repainted and complete with new carpet throughout, the home has a central main bathroom, an ensuite and a BIR or WIR in each bedroom. Extras including inverter heating/cooling, storage, a security system and courtyard, adjoining an automatic double carport with rear ROW access, ensure appeal. A stroll to transport, parkland, Coburg High and lively Sydney Road, you need to see it for yourself.

Description:
You Dont See this Every Day!
Where can you find an apartment of this size and style? Until now you couldnt. With two massive bedrooms both featuring excellent robe space. Generous open plan living and dining are well complimented by an expansive kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances.
An abundance of storage space, reverse cycle air conditioning and separate laundry provide another level of class all too often left out of the modern apartment. Two luxurious bathrooms with master bedroom getting the ensuite and your own private balcony to relax on, there truly is nothing left to do but kick back and enjoy.
Superb location featuring all forms of public transport within walking distance. With Sydney road on your doorstep there will be no shortage of restaurants, shops and cafes to entertain you for years to come. No need for a backyard when you have Merri Creek trail and Upfield bike path to stretch your legs.
With schools such as Coburg primary and Coburg high within a stones throw as well as Coburg Leisure Centre there is no end to the conveniences on offer. Perfect for the first home buyer, investor or downsizer its hard to go past this gem.

Description:
Classic Californian In A Premium Pocket
Classical Californian beauty enhanced by traditional features including leadlight windows, Baltic pine flooring, fireplace, bay window and ornate cornice a-top high ceilings, blends with a perfect position to introduce a lifestyle of excellence in this immediately appealing home.
Nestled in a coveted tree-lined pocket, it enjoys a premium position just a short walk from the bus, station, local shops, tram and the home-maker centre. Spacious open plan living pushes out from a stainless steel equipped contemporary kitchen and seamlessly spills through French doors onto a decked and paved undercover zone in a generous rear yard ready for private, low-upkeep alfresco enjoyment.
The three bedrooms (main with fireplace) are well served by a modern bathroom and a second toilet adjacent to the large laundry.
Throw in ducted heating and a split system unit, off street parking, established gardens and a 366m2 allotment (approx) that offers space to extend if desired (stca) and it's a winner on Webb.

Description:
Californian Bungalow With A Contemporary Heart
Much loved and proudly offered for the first time in seventeen years, this astutely renovated four bedroom, two bathroom Californian Bungalow is a celebration of modern family living and heritage charm. Stunning leadlight aspects, high ceilings and spotted gum polished floorboards complement an extended floor plan including substantial living zones where bi-fold doors and windows introduce an expansive alfresco deck and bring the outside in. Perfect for entertaining and relaxing, a large backyard offers respite from the daily grind and enjoys regular visits from Rainbow Lorikeets native to nearby Merri Creek parklands. Displaying 900mm stainless steel dual fuel cooker, Smeg dishwasher and abundant cabinetry, the gourmet kitchen will impress. Retreat to charming bedrooms, including one with ensuite and ornate open fireplace. The master boasts built-in-robes and links to a two way luxury bathroom. Features ducted heating/split system, laundry with attic space/storage and off-street parking. Stroll to picturesque Merri Creek trails, cafes, shops and schools, while trams to the CBD and beach pass by.

Description:
Townhouse Comfort With Alfresco Allure
Cherished by the same owner for over 35 years, this 2-bedroom townhouse
presents a fabulous opportunity for astute buyers seeking a pad with potential
enjoying wonderful proximity to the vibrancy of Brunswick and Coburg. Offering
comfortable living for today with plenty of scope for modernisation, the dual floor
layout is complemented by the alfresco allure of a sun-kissed terrace plus a
wraparound garden courtyard. Local parkland, the Upfield bike path, Moreland
Train Station, trams along Sydney Rd & Moreland Rd, CityLink access and the
impressive array of cuisine, shopping and amenities synonymous with a trendy
inner-north lifestyle are all within easy reach, ensuring this is an excellent option
for those with an eye on the future.
- Warm and welcoming living and dining areas, neat kitchen with gas cooking
- Wraparound garden courtyard with all the makings of a fabulous alfresco space
- Two upstairs bedrooms with built-in robes, bathroom with shower-over- bath
- Master (with A/C unit) to large sun-kissed terrace enjoying extensive views
- Entry-level powder/WC & laundry, gas heater in living areas, alarm system
- Undercover off-street car space plus handy adjacent visitor parking space
Insights: 1/343 Moreland Road, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Sophisticated Style For Superior Living
Sophisticated finishes tastefully executed, deliver superior living in this brand new two bedroom townhouse. Clean lines, neutral tones and splendid hardwood floors form an elegant backdrop to generous open plan living that opens to an inviting wrap around balcony and showcases a chic two tone kitchen boasting quality Ariston appliances, stone benchtops and stylish close cabinetry. This modern aesthetic is carried through to bedrooms with mirrored robes and a luxury bathroom boasting stone topped vanity and indulgent oversized shower. With split system heating/cooling and carport, in a trendy location where a short stroll finds vibrant Sydney Road specialty shopping and cafes, transport, Merri Creek parklands and trails, all a mere 7 kilometres to the CBD, exceptional modern living begins here.
Insights: 2/42 Moore Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2006 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Masterbuilt contemporary design, superb locale
This stylish rear town residence, one of only four, offers spacious and secure living minutes from Sydney Road cafes and all public transport options. A well zoned floor plan incorporates two double bedrooms with built-in robes, tiled semi-ensuite bathroom, spacious light-filled living/dining room with balcony and northerly views, custom kitchen with Blanco appliances and stone benchtops, powder room and laundry. Including designated parking, this immaculate home features polished hardwood floors, ample storage, split-system air-conditioning, alarm, intercom and tank irrigation.
Insights: 4/9 Blair Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Something To Smile About
A former dental surgery perfectly suited to medical professionals, this potential packed property supports a raft of options including conversion to a residence and developing the generous site of 557m2 (subject to council approval). An extended Californian Bungalow that has been optimised for use as a clinic, yet is versatile enough to suit various other purposes, it's zoned General Residential (GRZ1). Highlighting a reception area/office, waiting room, six consulting rooms and a sizeable two room laboratory, it's certainly big on space. Additional features include a kitchenette, sterilization room, store room, three powder rooms, ducted heating, air conditioning, front garden, outdoor sitting area, side driveway and car parking for multiple vehicles. Close to buses, trams, trains and Sydney Road, this is an opportunity to shape the future that you ought to see for yourself.
Insights: 37 O'Hea Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017.
